\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy defines the structure,
 scope,
 and limitations of decision-making authority within the Elko County Information Operations Department (ECIO).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all Information Operations personnel and to any County official,
 department,
 or entity interacting with the Information Operations Department in a managerial,
 technical,
 or support capacity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall hold primary operational and decision-making authority over technical services,
 cybersecurity,
 and infrastructure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall delegate administrative and operational authority as defined in Section 6 of this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall maintain the Separation of Duties Matrix and review it at least annually.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
County Manager
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall hold administrative oversight of the IT Director,
 including performance evaluation and policy ratification.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall not exercise operational authority over security controls.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall serve as the mediation authority for conflicts between administrative and operational authority as defined in Section 6.4.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assistant IT Director
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall hold standing delegated operational authority as defined in Section 6.2.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall serve as the primary operational decision-maker in the IT Director's absence,
 within the bounds of the standing written Delegation of Authority Order.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Human Resources (HR)
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall provide official onboarding and offboarding notifications as defined in Section 6.5.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall not direct or influence technical decisions or access control timelines.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Fiscal Affairs
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall oversee budgetary and procurement processes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall not prescribe technical standards or override IT design decisions.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All Information Operations Personnel
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall operate strictly within their designated role and authority as defined by department policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
Shall not assume authority beyond their assigned role without formal,
 written delegation.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
