caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Annual Policy Review and Maturity Scoring) and through the annual review of delegation records and the Separation of Duties Matrix required under Section 6 of this policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Enforcement
\series default
:
 The IT Director shall treat unauthorized assumption of authority,
 failure to document delegations,
 or exercise of authority beyond a delegation's defined scope as non-compliance and may initiate corrective action under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Policy Implementation,
 Enforcement,
 and Legal Alignment).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions to this policy shall be documented with written justification,
 approved in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 and processed as follows.
 Oral exceptions are not valid.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Operational Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions to operational delegation shall be approved in writing by the IT Director.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Governance Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions regarding decision rights or chain of command shall be approved by the County Manager in consultation with the IT Director.
 Governance exceptions shall not grant operational authority,
 alter security baselines,
 or authorize deviation from mandatory security controls.
 Governance exceptions shall not modify incident declaration authority,
 Incident Commander designation criteria,
 or operational decision rights during incident response as defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:4.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Incident Response Policy Overview).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Stand-in Restriction
\series default
:
 During the IT Director's absence,
 exceptions that would expand the authority of an acting administrative stand-in shall be deferred until the IT Director's return or escalated to the Board of County Commissioners.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
